Hello.

BProlog solution. I think that script do not exactly does what should. It
requires panel dimensions and width and heigt of the boards. As a result
script displays width of the boards an height (relative to bottom edge).

| ?- [wpc32].
consulting::wpc32.pl
yes

| ?- go((300,100)).
board 60,40 x:<0,60> y:+40
board 60,40 x:<0,60> y:+40
board 60,40 x:<60,120> y:+40
board 40,40 x:<60,100> y:+40
board 40,40 x:<100,140> y:+40
board 20,20 x:<0,20> y:+20
board 20,20 x:<20,40> y:+20
board 20,20 x:<40,60> y:+20
board 20,20 x:<60,80> y:+20
yes

| ?- go((200,200)).
board 60,40 x:<0,60> y:+40
board 60,40 x:<0,60> y:+40
board 60,40 x:<0,60> y:+40
board 40,40 x:<0,40> y:+40
board 40,40 x:<0,40> y:+40
board 20,20 x:<40,60> y:+20
board 20,20 x:<40,60> y:+20
board 20,20 x:<40,60> y:+20
board 20,20 x:<40,60> y:+20

Piotr.
